Connect and Sync Your Data to CRM Analytics
Amazon RDS Connection
Create a remote connection using one of the Amazon RDS connectors to bring data managed on the Amazon Relational Database Service into CRM Analytics.
Available Amazon RDS Connectors
AWS RDS Aurora MySQL
AWS RDS Aurora PostgreSQL
AWS RDS MariaDB
AWS RDS MySQL
AWS RDS PostgreSQL
AWS RDS SQL Server
Create the Connection
On the Data Manager Connections tab, click New Connection.
Click the name of the connector, and click Next.
Enter the connector settings.
Setting	DESCRIPTION
Connection Name	Identifies the connections.
Developer Name	API name for the connection.
Description	Description of the connection for internal use.
Database	Name of the database that you’re connecting to.
JDBC Connection URL	
Username	User name to connect to the database.
Schema	Schema name for the database.
Password	Password to connect to the database.
Filter Data Synced to CRM Analytics
Exclude unnecessary or sensitive data from syncing to CRM Analytics with data sync filters.
Amazon RDS Connector Considerations
Connected object names must start with a letter and contain only letters, digits, or underscores. Object names can’t end with an underscore.
This connector can sync up to 20 million rows or 10 GB per object, whichever limit it reaches first.
Columns of datatype JSON are not supported.
title: Connecting Amazon RDS to CRM Analytics
